{"title": "ESG Specialist", "link": "https://remotar.com.br/vagas/esg-specialist-esolidar/", "type": " Vaga tambm para PCD", "company": "esolidar", "category": " Outras reas", "date": "2022-03-30T11:00:38-03:00", "description": " We are looking for an ESG Specialist to lead esolidar ESG strategy, including being the interface with our customers, so they can use our platform to its full potential. Are you ready to do meaningful work that makes an impact?Who we areSince 2013 esolidar has been on a mission to revolutionize positive impact. Esolidar delivers ESG and CSR management tools to some of the worlds most exciting companies. We help them do good and measure their actions through our easy-to-use and engaging platform, accessible to everyone, wherever and whenever they need it.We do this by listening to the people we serve and acting on what we hear, creating the solutions they need.We do this, and we do so much moreWe have a mission-driven culture of purpose and passion that makes a positive difference in the world. Our team is 100% remote and distributed between Portugal and Brazil.Esolidar has served over 90,000 people in 4+ countries and companies like TAP Air Portugal, Rock in Rio, Accor Hotels, and Tetley.The roleTo help us on our mission, we are looking for an ESG (environmental, social, and governance) Specialist to join our growing team. Youll collaborate with all departments, defining and implementing an ESG strategy in-house and as a consultant for our customers, using our platform and proposing changes and improvements when required.The work is challenging but incredibly rewarding. This is a chance to make your mark and seize the growing opportunity for ESG technology.What youll doLead, promote and execute esolidar strategic, core ESG, and sustainability initiatives;Lead efforts on applying for certifications, sustainability reporting based on indexes (B Corp, Carbon Disclosure Project (CDP), Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG), Global Reporting Initiative (GRI), International &lt;IR&gt; Framework, ISE, etc.), and greenhouse gas emissions inventory;Support internal communication to make key functions and employees aware of esolidar sustainability initiatives and how different functions support the achievement of esolidar sustainability goals;Maintain consistency in quantitative and qualitative sustainability information across various communication platforms;Gather the relevant information to build ESG case studies;Perform analysis of external assessment scores which will support the improvement of existing and drive the development of new sustainability programs from existing customers;Develop with customers systematic frameworks and processes that analyze ESG risks and opportunities;Project manage customer requests on materiality assessments, sustainability reporting, and 3rd party assurance;Transform the ESG information into ready-to-use templates for the tech team;Research sustainability trends and always keep updated with ESG market best practices.Who you areYou live within the Brazilian or Portuguese timezone (UTC-3 to UTC+1);Minimum of a bachelors degree education;At least 3 years of experience in an ESG, CSR, or Sustainability focused role;Fluent in English and Portuguese;Demonstrated success in ESG KPI development, goal setting, measurement, tracking, and reporting;Experience creating successful partnerships with cross-functional internal and external teams for implementation of cohesive integrated ESG programs, best practices;Demonstrated success with cohesive analysis and assessment of impact using both key quantitative and qualitative data points;Background on leading sustainability reporting and/ or strategy development projects in an in-house role, or in a consulting role;Strong business acumen and knowledge of ESG goal setting, disclosures, best-in-class sustainability practices;Ability to build relationships, both internally and externally;Critical thinking, resilient, can-do attitude, and solution-driven;Passionate about learning new skills.It will be a nice plus if you haveExperience with Excel, and managing databases or other data repositories, likewise, some experience in development with programming languages;Other European languages will be a plus.Rewards &amp; BenefitsFlexible working hours (we trust you to work enough hours to do your job well, at times that suit you and your team);Flexible working from home policy. We are 100% fully remote, and we will stay that way for the foreseeable future (we also have a physical office space in Braga, Portugal, if you prefer to work that way);Flexible sick leave policy (take the time you need to feel better or take care of a sick family member within reason);22 days of paid vacation + 4 days off for Carnival, Christmas, New Years Eve, and your birthday (because we love what we do, but we also love vacation!);Matching donations program (when you donate money to a charity or equivalent, esolidar will make a matching gift to that charity on your behalf);A day for you to give back to the community (You can take one day off every year to volunteer for a charitable organization of your choice. Sometimes, we schedule these as a team);Meal Allowance;Career progression (we are currently building open and detailed career ladders);All equipment you may need. To build a great product, you need great gear (well provide you with a computer, a monitor, accessories, and any software you need to do your job as well as possible);A stimulating work environment and a chance to change the world (literally!).Personal compensation management (you choose your benefits )Health and dental insurance;Technology spending in Apple and other tech stores;Childcare vouchers;Transport Card;Professional Training;Retirement &amp; Investment;Health &amp; Well-being;Senior Expenses;School Expenses;Exclusive discounts + tax-free products and discounted services from the likes of Apple, Holmes Place, etcA few points in closingWere constantly evaluating our perks to enhance them for our team, and we tend to provide some extras that are not listed here;Some of the perks listed above will be considered taxable income depending on how you use them and the tax laws aligned with where you reside.Diversity and inclusion at esolidarAt esolidar, our mission is to improve lives through dependable and straightforward tools that help make a difference.Weve set an audacious goal: to make esolidar the most diverse, equitable, and inclusive workplace on the planet.We believe diversity drives innovation. So were building a culture where difference is valued. We hire under equal opportunity, irrespective of gender, ethnicity, religion, belief, disability, sexual orientation, pregnancy, maternity, or background.As part of our positive strategy, everyone has the opportunity to speak up and participate, grow and share ideas. We strive to be mindful by being aware of our surroundings, acknowledging the impact others have on us and our impact on them.Be yourself. We like it that way."},
